The paper deals with tool path planning for free form surfaces, which is a common problem in computer graphics and robotics. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques and energy functionals, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for tool path optimization, which involves considering different objectives simultaneously, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
